 IN RABBIT MQ WHAT IT MEANS BY RPC:-
 What Is a Reply Message in RabbitMQ?
 Reply message = response sent back to original sender through a queue
 It is used in something called:
 RPC (Remote Procedure Call) over messaging

 so normally we do :-
 producer  -> queue   -> consumer
 normally we do this
 @RabbitListener(queues = MessagingConfig.DLQ_QUEUE)
 public void consumeDlq(EmailEventDto dto,Channel channel,Message message){


 but in this if consumer listner method kai return kare it means e pachu consumer to procuder mokalvanu
 che evu lage MQTT ne
  @RabbitListener(queues = MessagingConfig.DLQ_QUEUE)
  public ResponseEntity<?> consumeDlq(EmailEventDto dto,Channel channel,Message message){
  so ama apde kai retrun kariee toh Rabbit ne evu lage ke pachu have ane procuder ne mokalvanu che
        Use Case	                     Why Reply Needed
        Payment validation	             Need success/failure
        Inventory check	                 Need stock count
        OTP verification	             Need confirmation
        Microservice to microservice     sync call	Need result
    but for REPLAY apde set karvu pade producer side thi
    reply-to property AA SET KARVU PADE
    otherwise set karya vagar return karse consumer site thi toh error apse





